# Class: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0200006> (biexponential transformation)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0200006> "This type of transformation is typically used in flow cytometry."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000114> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0200006> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000122>)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0200006> "A biexponential transformation is a data transformation that, for each (one dimensional) real number input x, outputs an approximation (found, e.g. with the Newton's method) to a solution y of the equation B(y)-x=0, where B denotes a b transformation."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000117> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0200006> "Elisabetta Manduchi"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000117> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0200006> "Joseph Spliden"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000117> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0200006> "Ryan Brinkman"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0200006> "biexponential transformation"@en)
SubClassOf(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0200006> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0200000>)
SubClassOf(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0200006> ObjectIntersectionOf(ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000299> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000451>) ObjectSomeValuesFrom(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0000417> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0200167>)))
